---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MethodologySummary from '../components/MethodologySummary.astro';
import { visibleCities } from '../lib/cities';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="CourtScope | Racial gaps in criminal sentencing"
  description="CourtScope examines public sentencing records to measure racial gaps in incarceration and sentence length across similar cases."
>
  <section class="hero national-hero">
    <div class="shell hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Public sentencing data, explained</p>
        <h1>See the patterns behind criminal sentences.</h1>
        <p class="lede">CourtScope studies many similar cases to measure racial gaps in two outcomes: <strong>who is sentenced to incarceration</strong> and <strong>how long incarceration sentences are</strong>.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button" href="/cities">Choose a city</a>
          <button class="button secondary" type="button" data-tour-open>How to use CourtScope</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-score-card" aria-label="Disparity Score guide">
        <p class="score-name">Disparity Score</p>
        <strong class="hero-score-number">0–100</strong>
        <p><b>Low numbers</b> mean smaller measured racial gaps. <b>High numbers</b> mean bigger measured racial gaps.</p>
        <div class="mini-scale" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Start with the basics</p>
        <h2>What is this site?</h2>
        <p>CourtScope is a public-interest research tool. It organizes court records so people can inspect sentencing patterns that are difficult to see one case at a time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3 explainer-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>What is it for?</h3>
          <p>It helps voters, journalists, researchers, lawyers, community members, and public officials ask better questions about sentencing.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>What does it measure?</h3>
          <p>It measures adjusted racial gaps in incarceration and sentence length across qualifying cases assigned to the same judge.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>What does it not do?</h3>
          <p>It does not decide whether one case was appropriate, tell anyone how to vote, or make a finding about a judge’s motives.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Read the number plainly</p>
        <h2>Understanding the Disparity Score</h2>
        <p>The score is descriptive, not a personal rating. It summarizes the largest measured racial gap found in the two sentencing outcomes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="score-legend">
        <div class="legend-small"><strong>0–29</strong><span>Smaller racial gaps</span></div>
        <div class="legend-moderate"><strong>30–59</strong><span>Moderate racial gaps</span></div>
        <div class="legend-big"><strong>60–100</strong><span>Bigger racial gaps</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="legal-limitation"><em>A measured disparity does not prove racism, discrimination, intent, misconduct, or whether any individual sentence was appropriate.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell"><MethodologySummary /></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">How to use the site</p>
        <h2>Five steps from score to context</h2>
      </div>
      <ol class="numbered-steps">
        <li><strong>Choose a city.</strong><span>Each city has its own courts, records, coverage window, and data status.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Open a judge card.</strong><span>Read the score, label, number of qualifying cases, and data strength.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Open “Why this score?”</strong><span>See which outcome produced the larger measured gap and the most important group comparisons.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Compare only within the same court.</strong><span>Different courts may handle different cases and should not be treated as one league table.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Read the methodology.</strong><span>Use the full method and data limitations before drawing conclusions.</span></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Available jurisdictions</p>
        <h2>Choose a city</h2>
        <p>A city dashboard may be visible as a clearly labeled fixture preview before official records are published. Public downloads remain locked until the city passes every data gate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        {visibleCities.map((city) => (
          <article class="card city-card">
            <div>
              <span class="city-status">{city.published ? 'Published' : 'Preview'}</span>
              <h3>{city.name}</h3>
              <p>{city.notice}</p>
            </div>
            <a class="button" href={`/${city.slug}`}>Open {city.name}</a>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="shell grid grid-2">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Can this prove discrimination?</p>
        <h2>No. It can identify patterns that deserve examination.</h2>
        <p>Statistical patterns may raise important questions. They cannot, by themselves, establish why a difference occurred or whether a legal violation took place.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Open and expandable</p>
        <h2>Inspect the method. Help add a city.</h2>
        <p>CourtScope publishes its methodology, data requirements, limitations, and source code so the work can be reviewed and improved.</p>
        <div class="actions"><a class="button light" href="/open-source">Open source</a><a class="button outline-light" href="/add-cities">Bring CourtScope to your city</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
